            <h3>
             Bloomberg
            </h3>
            <span class="headdate">
             Feb 28
            </span>
            <span class="excrpt">
             <p>
              Electricity infrastructure safety regulations are products of a time when fires were less common, said Prof. Severin Borenstein, E.T. Grether Chair in Business Administration and Public Policy. "The way we do grid safety is not the way we do food safety or airline safety," he said. He said a better model would require oversight bodies with the money and manpower to carry out their own inspections.
             </p>
            </span>
           </div>
          </a>
          <a href="https://poetsandquants.com/2019/02/21/10-remarkable-women-mbas-to-watch/?pq-category=students%2F3%2F&amp;utm_source=Haas%20in%20the%20Headlines&amp;utm_campaign=d4b3bc2a90-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2018_03_02_COPY_14&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_term=0_f3a179feae-d4b3bc2a90-321541577" target="_blank">
